I don't usually write reviews, but after visiting Duke, I felt I had to share what a truly unforgettable evening it was.

From the moment we walked in, the atmosphere captivated us: elegant, welcoming, and with an energy that was noticeable as soon as you walked through the door. The service was excellent throughout. The servers were incredibly friendly, attentive without being pushy, explaining each dish in detail and taking care of every little gesture to make us feel comfortable.

And then there's the sushi... wonderful. Each piece was a small spectacle: fresh fish, perfect cuts, and flavor combinations that surprised without losing balance. You can tell that at Duke, they don't just make sushi, they celebrate it.

But what really made the evening special was the mixologist. Not only does he know what he's doing, which is saying something (each cocktail was a work of art), but he also does it with a friendliness and joy that is contagious. He recommended drinks based on our tastes and got them all right. We ended up staying longer just because of the good vibes he conveyed.

Duke isn't just a restaurant; it's a complete experience. If you're looking for quality, a great atmosphere, and people who enjoy doing their jobs well, you can't miss this restaurant.

text:
una experiencia decepcionante en un restaurante que aspira al lujo

Fuimos tres personas a comer a este restaurante, cuya propuesta y precio (unos 90-100‚ÄØ‚Ç¨ por persona) hacen pensar en una experiencia gastron√≥mica de alto nivel. Por eso mismo, la decepci√≥n fue a√∫n mayor.

Llegamos a las 14:45 y, a los cinco minutos, nos tomaron nota de la bebida. Pedimos agua y un c√≥ctel. Diez minutos despu√©s, solo nos hab√≠an tra√≠do el agua, as√≠ que aprovechamos para pedir tambi√©n una botella de vino y hacer la comanda completa: varios entrantes, un plato de pescado y un maki de carne como cierre. El vino lleg√≥, pero el c√≥ctel nunca apareci√≥ durante la comida. Solo nos lo sirvieron al final, como disculpa.

Tardaron 30 minutos en servir el primer plato, una tempura de verduras con carabineros, que lleg√≥ con una sorpresa muy desagradable: tres pelos incrustados en la tempura. El camarero se disculp√≥ r√°pidamente, alegando que se trataba de pelos de una brocha de cocina (lo cual ya es bastante preocupante). Nos prometi√≥ repetir el plato, pero lo que trajeron fue solo una tempura de verduras, sin carabinero. En un restaurante de este nivel, cuesta entender c√≥mo pueden decidir repetir un plato mal servido y, aun as√≠, no completarlo adecuadamente.

Lo siguiente en llegar fue el maki de carne, que, adem√°s de estar fuera de orden (era el √∫ltimo plato del men√∫), lleg√≥ fr√≠o. De sabor, estaba bien, pero no fue suficiente para compensar el mal desarrollo del servicio. A medida que avanzaba la comida, los tiempos segu√≠an descompasados y, aunque intentaron compensarlo con unos nigiris extra, fue un gesto insuficiente, ya que hab√≠amos pedido platos suficientes y lo que fallaba no era la cantidad, sino la organizaci√≥n y ejecuci√≥n.

Por si fuera poco, en mitad del almuerzo se fue la luz solo en nuestra zona del comedor, y pasamos unos diez minutos comiendo a media luz, con la l√°mpara de mesa encendida como √∫nica iluminaci√≥n.

Otro detalle importante fue el servicio del vino: la botella no se dej√≥ cerca de nosotros, por lo que, cuando se nos vaciaba la copa, no pod√≠amos servirnos y tampoco hab√≠a personal pendiente para hacerlo. Algo tan b√°sico en un restaurante de este nivel deber√≠a estar m√°s que controlado.

A nivel gastron√≥mico, la comida no destac√≥ especialmente. En nuestra opini√≥n, no super√≥ el nivel de otros restaurantes japoneses de la isla. Puede que el c√∫mulo de errores empa√±ara la percepci√≥n, pero, en cualquier caso, la experiencia no justific√≥ ni de lejos el precio.

La cuenta final fue de 392‚ÄØ‚Ç¨ para tres personas, y eso que nos invitaron al postre y al c√≥ctel, que finalmente sirvieron al terminar la comida.

En resumen: una experiencia muy por debajo de las expectativas, con errores de servicio y cocina dif√≠ciles de justificar en un restaurante que presume de excelencia.
textTranslated:
A disappointing experience at a restaurant that aspires to luxury

Three of us went to this restaurant for lunch, whose menu and price (around ‚Ç¨90-100 per person) suggest a high-end dining experience. For this reason, the disappointment was even greater.

We arrived at 2:45 p.m., and five minutes later, our drinks were taken. We ordered water and a cocktail. Ten minutes later, only the water had been brought, so we took the opportunity to also order a bottle of wine and place our full order: several starters, a fish dish, and a beef maki to close the meal. The wine arrived, but the cocktail never appeared during the meal. It was only served at the end, as an apology.

It took 30 minutes for the first course, a vegetable tempura with prawns, to be served, which came with a very unpleasant surprise: three hairs embedded in the tempura. The waiter quickly apologized, claiming they were hairs from a kitchen brush (which is worrying enough). He promised to repeat the dish, but what they brought was only vegetable tempura, without shrimp. In a restaurant of this caliber, it's hard to understand how they can decide to repeat a poorly served dish and still not complete it properly.

The next thing to arrive was the beef maki, which, in addition to being out of order (it was the last dish on the menu), arrived cold. It tasted good, but it wasn't enough to compensate for the poor service. As the meal progressed, the timing continued to drag, and although they tried to compensate with extra nigiri, it was an insufficient gesture, since we had ordered enough dishes and what was lacking wasn't the quantity, but the organization and execution.

As if that weren't enough, halfway through lunch, the power went out only in our dining area, and we spent about ten minutes eating in dim light, with the table lamp on as the only lighting.

Another important detail was the wine service: the bottle wasn't left near us, so when our glass was empty, we couldn't pour ourselves, and there was no staff on hand to do it. Something so basic in a restaurant of this level should be more than adequately controlled.

On a culinary level, the food didn't particularly stand out. In our opinion, it didn't exceed the standards of other Japanese restaurants on the island. Perhaps the accumulation of errors tarnished the perception, but in any case, the experience didn't nearly justify the price.

The final bill was ‚Ç¨392 for three people, even though we were treated to dessert and a cocktail, which were ultimately served at the end of the meal.

In short: an experience far below expectations, with service and cooking errors that are difficult to justify in a restaurant that prides itself on excellence.

La carta no difiere mucho de la oferta del kiki y tanto los cocineros como parte de los camareros y metre tambi√©n viene de abajo. Me esperaba una experiencia algo m√°s diferente pero es innegable que se come muy bien.

textTranslated:
A new Japanese restaurant from the same group as Kiki and Kabuki de Las Palmas. It's located in the Mencey Hotel, and both the decor and the restaurant itself are spectacular. Divided over two floors, it's spacious and comfortable.

The menu doesn't differ much from Kiki's, and both the chefs and some of the waiters and waitresses also come from downstairs. I expected a slightly different experience, but it's undeniable that the food is very good.

- Usuzukuris
We ordered the salmon, white fish, and tuna. Each one is better than the last; it's a great option to start.

- Shibuya
Another of the maki dishes that never fails. Tempura and topped with ceviche tartar.

- Salmon and quail egg nigiri
Both are spectacular. A simple bite, but delicious.

- Red shrimp taco
Very good. It comes on a corn tortilla and is generously portioned. A bit salty, but exquisite.

- Maki sake duke
The discovery of the night. I hadn't tried it before and it was amazing.

- Uramaki rippongi
Another good maki, but flatter compared to the previous one and the Shibuya.

We tried a cocktail called Hanami, which was amazing. A great place to order several.

The service is fantastic. Very attentive and friendly as always. A wonderful team.

I had high expectations, and they met them. As I mentioned at the beginning, I was probably expecting a slightly different menu, but I like Kiki's menu so much that I still left amazed. It's hard to find a better one.
Regarding prices, I'd say between ‚Ç¨80 and ‚Ç¨100 per person, including wine.

100% recommended.
